What you need to know:

Kadondi, 44, passed away on Sunday at St Francis Hospital in Kasarani, Nairobi where she was being treated following a short illnessFootball Kenya Federation president Nick Mwendwa took to Twitter to condole with her familyThe long-serving goalkeeper played for Starlets from 1995 to 2012 and featured in Africa Women Cup of Nations (Awcon) qualifiers against Djibouti and Cameroon in 2006 and 2007 respectively.